Samurai Chain 🤍⛓️💗
It makes my heart so happy when someone comes back to collect another piece from me. 🥰

I met @rosemarydirects a lifetime ago, back when I was making chains between shifts as a waitress at Esperanto on Ave C in New York. 

I’ll never forget sitting for dinner with her and her husband Nestor (aka Nestorious), when she told me she had spoken with a good friend about my glass work. I was shocked to learn he was a well known jeweler, famous actually (!) and he had some advice for me. 😳 He sent a detailed list of questions to ask myself about starting a jewelry business; How many employees did I want? What did my business plan look like?? He even had tips and suggestions to consider. It was all kind of over my head at the time, but I later saw it as a pivotal moment that changed my perspective of what I was capable of and helped give me the confidence to pursue glass as a career.

Dear Nestor and Rosemary, thank you for believing in me back then and returning to support me & my glasswork again after all these years. 🙏🙏🙏 So much love to you both. 💞 @rosemarydirects

Have you ever wanted to take a glass chain making class with me? Your chance is now! I’m doing a weekend workshop in downtown Brooklyn @UrbanGlass_nyc July 14-16th. There are only a few spots left!! To sign up go to:

https://urbanglass.org/classes/detail/chain-making

🔗🔗🔗🔗🔗🔗🔗🔗🔗🔗🔗

Learn how to make stunning borosilicate glass chains with Cha Cha Chainz! In this flameworking class, you will explore techniques for melting and bending clear and colored rods to create beautiful, wearable works of art. All skill levels are welcomed and encouraged to join. We will discuss symmetrical connections and tips to keep your chains from cracking by inspecting areas of stress and tension within the glass. Additionally, you will be given the opportunity to combine glass with other materials to create unique, exquisite pieces. Don’t miss out on this opportunity to make something truly extraordinary; so bring some of your own jewelry for inspiration and let’s mix it up and get creative!  This Class Meets:  Fri July 14 : 6-9pm Sat July 15 & Sun July 16 : 
10am-6pm both days

What to Expect: Class will be divided by demonstrations, individual instruction and plenty of practice time. By the end of the session, students should have a complete chain and the confidence to continue advancing their skills independently.

Last night I attended the @Lagos_Jewelry debut of their men’s collection at @theNedNomad in NYC. I got to meet such wonderful people with the brand and learned about jewelry grade ceramic, which I have never seen incorporated with metals before.

Repost via @themichiganglassproject : We are presenting this year’s “Devi of the Autumnal Renewal” for the first time at The Great Fall Gathering on 11/11. This psychedelic beauty was brought to life at the 2023 Michigan Glass Project by glass greats @Banjoglass, @pipemaker, @Saltglass, @Eusheen, @NikoCray, @Windstar_glass, @ChaCha_Chainz, and @Frompy.

No ordinary creation, her glass form shines with an ethereal glow and her intricate details sparkle like a thousand stars on a clear night. The 2023 Devi is a true visual and functional masterpiece.
The Devi of the Autumnal Renewal will be featured in our Silent Auction at the Great Fall Gathering. If you’re interested in this piece and want to place bids but are unable to attend, please DM us for proxy and online bidding info.

I had the opportunity to revisit my first chandelier installation, which I worked on with @cleodglassworks. It was truly amazing to see its completion with the smoke/charcoal colored leaves that were added later. The darker hues perfectly complemented the clients’ interior designs, inspired by an incredible green and black marble slab that served as the bar countertop at the base of the staircase.

Being a part of this team has been an invaluable learning experience. I have come to appreciate the significance of every single part and piece in ensuring a successful installation. I am sincerely grateful for these opportunities and I can’t wait to do more with Cleod Glassworks. 

Thank you wholeheartedly for welcoming me into your team! 🙏🥹
